  "title": "QS ENGINEER (POST TENDER)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u><br /><strong>Contract Administration:</strong> Managing the contract to ensure compliance by all parties.</p><p><strong>Progress Claims & Payments:</strong> Evaluating, certifying, and processing interim payments and progress claims from subcontractors and suppliers.</p><p><strong>Variation Order (VO) Management:</strong> Identifying, negotiating, and finalizing variation orders (additions or omissions) to the contract sum.</p><p><strong>Cost Control & Reporting:</strong> Monitoring project costs against the budget, producing monthly cost reports, and forecasting final project costs.</p><p><strong>Subcontractor Management:</strong> Preparing subcontractor documents, purchasing agreements, and managing subcontract payments.</p><p><strong>Final Accounts:</strong> Negotiating and settling final accounts with clients, consultants, and subcontractors.</p><p><strong>Claims Management:</strong> Handling Extension of Time (EOT) claims and managing contractual disputes.</p><p><strong>Site Liaison:</strong> Working with project managers, engineers, and site teams to monitor site progress and identify cost implications. </p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor’s Degree or Diploma in Quantity Surveying, Building, or Civil Engineering.</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Usually requires 2–5+ years of experience in post-contract QS roles, often with a main contractor or consultant.</li><li><strong>Skills: </strong>Proficiency in MS Office (especially Excel) and specialized QS software, strong knowledge of construction contracts & meticulous with strong negotiation and numerical skills. </li></ul>",
